================================================================================
                    RCG — Relational Cosmological Geometry
================================================================================

ABSTRACT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Relational Cosmological Geometry (RCG) treats large-scale CMB structure as
emerging from relational densities ρ₊ and ρ₋ via the geometry operator 𝓖 and
screening length d_s. It provides a unified geometric origin for the low-ℓ
anomalies (quadrupole-octopole alignment, hemispherical asymmetry, power
deficit, lack of large-angle correlation, parity asymmetry, Cold Spot) without
extra parameters. The same fit to low-ℓ temperature determines lensing
modulation α₁, α₂ and other signatures.

================================================================================
CORE COMPONENTS
================================================================================

1. Relational Densities
   Δρ(x) = ρ₊(x) - ρ₋(x)          (imbalance)
   τ(x)  = ρ₊(x) + ρ₋(x)          (total tension)

2. Geometry Operator
   𝓖 Ψ = -∇²Ψ + μ Δρ(x) Ψ + ν (û · ∇Ψ)
   Lowest eigenmode: 𝓖 Ψ₀ = λ₀ Ψ₀
   Boundary projection: M_{2,3}(n̂) = Ψ₀(χ_*, n̂)   ← Q-boundary mode

3. Screening Length
   d_s(x) = d₀ exp[-α Δρ(x)/τ(x)]

4. Propagator & Kernel
   G(d;x) = exp(-d / d_s(x))
   K(θ) = ∫ dχ W(χ) exp(-d(χ,θ) / d_s(χ,n̂))

5. Low-ℓ Temperature Field
   T(n̂) = T_iso(n̂) + A_Q M_{2,3}(n̂) + A_D (d̂ · n̂)

6. Lensing Potential (Closure)
   φ(n̂) = φ_iso + β_Q M_{2,3}(n̂) + β_D (d̂ · n̂)
   with β_Q = k_Q A_Q , β_D = k_D A_D
   → C_L^{φφ}(n̂) = C_L^{φφ,iso} [1 + α₁ Y_{1m}(n̂) + α₂ Y_{2m}(n̂)]

7. Cold Spot
   Localized ρ₋ defect (Δρ << 0) → short d_s → tension scar

================================================================================
FULL PIPELINE
================================================================================

Step 1: Fit A_Q, A_D, d̂ to observed low-ℓ a_{ℓm}^T (ℓ ≤ 30)
Step 2: Solve 𝓖Ψ₀ = λ₀Ψ₀ → M_{2,3}(n̂)
Step 3: Compute d_s → K(θ)
Step 4: Derive α₁ ∝ k_D A_D , α₂ ∝ k_Q A_Q
Step 5: Compute ISW contributions from same A_Q, A_D
Step 6: Enforce bounds:
       |α₁|, |α₂| ≲ 0.01
       |ΔC_ℓ^{TT}/C_ℓ^{TT}| ≪ 0.01 for ℓ > 100
       Weak κ, subtle EE/EB around Cold Spot

================================================================================
COMPACT SUMMARY
================================================================================

Low-ℓ CMB = global Q-boundary mode M_{2,3}
          + ∇(ρ₊/ρ₋) gradient
          + spectral gap
          + Π-chiral spectrum
          + D_ρ₋ defect (Cold Spot)

All generated from single operator 𝓖 and screening d_s(Δρ/τ).
Fit low-ℓ T → predicts lensing α₁,α₂, polarization, ISW, high-ℓ residuals
with no extra parameters.

